Class Circle

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.geom.RectangularShape
      • java.awt.geom.Ellipse2D
        • java.awt.geom.Ellipse2D.Double
          • Circle
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.Shape, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

    public class Circle
extends java.awt.geom.Ellipse2D.Double
    Simple wrapper class to wrap a 2D Ellipse with two identical radii Such an ellipse is a circle.
    See Also:

      • Circle

        public Circle(int _x,
              int _y,
              int _radius,
              java.awt.Color _color,
              boolean _fill)
        Circle - constructor - uses ellipse constructor and radius as height and width. Allows user to specify to fill the circle. Also allows the user to specify the color for drawing and filling.
        Parameters:
        _x - the x position of the upper left corner of the enclosing box
        _y - the y position of the upper left corner of the enclosing box
        _radius - the radius of the circle ... used as height and width of the ellipse
        _color - the color to use for drawing and filling.
        _fill - boolean fill flag for the circle ... true means draw the circle filled
